Dmitry Medvedev, a close ally to Vladimir Putin, announced a plan to destroy Elon Musk's Starling satellites in a United Russia party document. The Kremlin believes the satellites were used to help the Ukrainian army sink the flagship of Russia's Black Sea fleet. It comes as the US announced a further $800 million package in military aid, which would for the first time include artillery pieces. Moscow, however, warned of "unpredictable consequences" if Washington and the allies keep supplying weapons to Kyiv.  FOLLOW THE LATEST UPDATE BELOW